    {
      "text": "Which of the following is first investigation to be done in patient with acute lower GI Bleeding with hemodynamic instability?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Colonoscopy"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Upper GI endoscopy"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Sigmoidoscopy"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Digital rectal examination"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is B: Upper GI endoscopy</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>In patients with Lower GI <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"41e858bf2816927771836d46c619b9\">bleeding</span> with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cdf4a197dd16927771881a652c8328\">hemodynamic</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"acb259200b16927771908888d1377c\">instability</span> first investigation done is UGI endoscopy</li>\n\t<li>In patients with Lower GI <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"41e858bf2816927771836d46c619b9\">bleeding</span> without <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cdf4a197dd16927771881a652c8328\">hemodynamic</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"acb259200b16927771908888d1377c\">instability</span> first investigation is colonoscopy.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"\" data-source=\"\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"245\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/dlwuBtz37V7O2PDKa73K1754993127.png\" width=\"700\" /></p>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [
        "https://image.prepladder.com/content/dlwuBtz37V7O2PDKa73K1754993127.png"
      ],
