      "explanation_audio_hin": "https://image.prepladder.com/content/oF5PG3bLhoPlejO0xe2A1755291618.mp3"
    },
    {
      "text": "Which of the following investigations is best for detecting lesions of active Crohn’s disease?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Wireless capsule endoscopy ​​​​​​​​​​​​​​"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "MR enterography"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "CT enterography"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Barium enema"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is A: Wireless <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"54635b1bf01692777183247ecff5e0\">capsule</span> endoscopy</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Wireless <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"54635b1bf01692777183247ecff5e0\">capsule</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a9e7c4b7051692777187a218b539d7\">endoscopy</span> allows direct <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"33ba8d60fb16927772029d1067e602\">visualization</span> of the entire small-bowel mucosa. The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"552e9ef8811692777186997018b858\">diagnostic</span> yield of detecting lesions suggestive of active CD is higher with WCE than CT or magnetic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"37b9856df8169277719716b550a15f\">resonance</span> enterography</li>\n</ul>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation_audio_eng": "https://image.prepladder.com/content/PI3YpC2wlGE45gQPzr671755291723.mp3",
      "explanation_audio_hin": "https://image.prepladder.com/content/UaauyaRLI37KnnXI8yL81755292152.mp3"
    },
    {
      "text": "Which of the following classification system is used exclusively for determination of severity of ulcerative colitis?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Truelove and Witts"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Montreal classification"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Vienna classification"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Marsh classification"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is A: Truelove and Witts</strong></p>\n\n<p>This is a closely worded question as Option A and B both are used. Option B is for extent and severity while Option A is<strong> exclusively for severity</strong> of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b118cf61a016927772018a179057ef\">ulcerative</span> colitis.</p>\n\n<p>True love and Witt’s classification</p>\n\n<table align=\"center\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black\">\n\t\t\t<p> </p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Mild</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Moderate</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Severe</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>Bowel movements (no. per day)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>Fewer than 4</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>4-6</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>Six or more plus at least one of the features of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8f2e7fd96116927771995b451b5c90\">systemic</span> upset </p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>Blood in stools</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>No more than small amounts of blood</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>Between mild and severe</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>Visible blood</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>Pyrexia (temperature >than 37.8∘ C)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>No</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>No</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>Yes</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>Pulse rate greater than 90 bpm </p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>No</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>No</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>Yes</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>Anemia </p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>No</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>No</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>Yes</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>Erythrocyte <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d53a6ee0c81692777198aeb94eb4ca\">sedimentation</span> rate (mm/hour) </p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>30 or below</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>30 or below</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none\">\n\t\t\t<p>Above 30</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p> </p>",
