    {
      "text": "Patient with ulcerative colitis presents with ulcerated lesions with violaceous edges surrounded by a margin of erythema on both shins. Diagnosis is?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Erythema nodosum"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Pyoderma gangrenosum"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Pyoderma vegetans"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Sweet syndrome"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is B: Pyoderma gangrenosum</strong></p>\n\n<p>Pyoderma gangrenosum begins as painful pustules or nodules which rapidly progress into deep ulcers with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"57d8f3ea831692777202e8adc0cee9\">violaceous</span> /purple margins and undermined edges surrounded by an erythematous margin.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Incorrect Options:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Option A - <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f0f3e105661692777187df507b1f26\">Erythema</span> nodosum:</strong> Presents as tender, red or purple nodules usually on the shins, but these are <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bfa856c77716927771939978c5afd0\">nodular</span> lesions without <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"50f4196df6169277720181ef605c33\">ulceration</span> or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"57d8f3ea831692777202e8adc0cee9\">violaceous</span> borders.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Option C - Pyoderma vegetans:</strong> A much rarer <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5be6ed908e16927772017095bae56c\">vegetative</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0efdcdc9e01692777201003c81c85a\">variant</span> with verrucous, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5be6ed908e16927772017095bae56c\">vegetative</span> plaques</p>\n\n<p><strong>Option</strong> <strong>D - Sweet syndrome</strong>: Presents with tender, erythematous plaques or nodules often accompanied by fever and leukocytosis</p>",
